solution: ```class Solution:
    def smallestSubsequence(self, s: str) -> str:
        last = {c: i for i, c in enumerate(s)}
        stack = []
        seen = set()
        for i, c in enumerate(s):
            if c in seen:
                continue
            while stack and c < stack[-1] and i < last[stack[-1]]:
                seen.remove(stack.pop())
            stack.append(c)
            seen.add(c)
        return ''.join(stack)
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Greedy stack construction with monotonic ordering. Track last occurrence of each character to ensure every popped character can still be placed later. Guarantees lexicographically smallest subsequence containing all distinct characters exactly once.

